 6% (gross) in cash, for investments of £1,000 - £250,000. Our initial aim, to raise £15m, was reached early due to a phenomenal response that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">resulted in the Bond being over-subscribed - a gratifying endorsement of the Nuffield Health proposition in a depressed bond market. Ultimately the Bond raised £18m to help us make a real difference to the future of healthcare. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:10pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">19.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Nuffield Health has the bes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">t balance sheet in the private health sector (compared to gym or private hospital operators). We are the least leveraged businesses in the industry and our debt represents less than 25% of our overall value. Alexander Harrison, Director Strategic Debt Fina</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">nce, Barclays Commercial Bank, 2008: “Nuffield Health has a very strong balance sheet with a low ratio of debt relative to the sector, further reinforcing their market position.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:10pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">20.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">13% of revenue comes from products and services that cost less than £1 a day.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Hospitals and medical </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">centres</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent: